<br>
However, once they reach the age of adulthood, and are legally able to make their choices for themselves, then your control ends. Also, how is it &quot;forcing children into immoral life styles&quot; to tell them that everyone is different and unique, and just because someone is different or does things differently doesn't make them bad or wrong? Intolerance is intolerance, whether it be racial, preference, religion, anything. Wasn't this country founded on the idea of TOLERANCE? So how is it &quot;moral&quot; to want to teach a child IN-tolerance?<br>
<br>
If a teacher were to tell your child, &quot;You should be gay because all straight people are bad and wrong&quot; then that teacher should be fired. They're giving your child a value judgement, and that's wrong. A teacher telling your child, &quot;People who are gay are just as good and special as anyone else, they just make different choices than other people, but everyone is different and unique and their choice is no more right or wrong than anyone elses&quot; is saying the lifestyle exists, but is NOT saying it's better OR worse than any other, and that's the big difference.<br>
<br>
You as a PARENT could tell your child that you disagree with that lifestyle choice, and give him your reasons, that's part of BEING a parent. But a school is not there to pass on morality, nor should it be. Especially considering YOUR morality is not MY morality. The teaching of morality is done in the home, but must be tempered with tolerance. If you want to live in a land of Intolerance, I am sure there's plenty of dictatorships around the world you could move to.<br>
