<br>
Wrong!  It does not say, no one religion shall be places above another.  It says, the government shall not have the authority to control religion.  The populace of that government is therefore allowed to determine on its own, which religion it tends to think on best.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Christianity teaches Drugs are Bad. MANY others do not. Why are those others forced to follow the tenets of a different religion? Christianity teaches Homosexuality is Bad. MANY Others do not. So why is there society-wide prejudice against people who happen to be gay? Aren't their individual rights being trampled on to marry or OPENLY be in the military, if they follow a faith that says their lifestyle is perfectly OK? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Forsaking my personal viewpoints on the subjects, here is my take (my opinion on why the churches formulate their opinions on the topics) the current Christian doctrine forcludes and forsakes the issues:<br>
<br>
1)  Homosexuality does not promote the advancement of the species via procreation.  Its a given biological fact due to our form of sexual creation, that two members of the same sex cannot procreate.  The bible stipulates that man and women shall 'join together' ( I beleive those are the exact words) in family.  Therefore, basic judeo-christian doctrine has taken the stance that homosexuality is bad.<br>
<br>
2)  Drugs affect both the taker and in many cases those that are not the taker.  Its proven that IV drug users transmit more readily disease than those that do not.  Its proven that drugs do impair judgement.  Its proven fact that with impaired judgement, many people get hurt.  The bible stipulates that man should remain clear of mind and judgement.  Therefore, basic judeo-christian doctrine has taken the stance that drugs are bad.  <br>
<br>
Now I agree with both of those by the way.  However, I do not think this is being FORCE FED down your throats.  It is established in almost (notice I said ALMOST) every country in the world that drugs are bad.  It is a known fact that two members of the same sex cannot procreate the species.  Given that reasoning, it is fairly clear why these issues would be taught at an early age.  This is societal teachings, not governmental.  You guys are confusing the two.  The government always reflects the society in which it represents, remember the words, &quot;of the people, by the people, for the people&quot;? <br>
<br>
Hope this better makes my stance clear, that the current administrations is only projecting its viewpoint, no differently than the previous administration did with its own viewpoint.  The administration is not mandating religion or societal views, its using its own moralities and beliefs to affect its term of office and decision making process.  Religion has a part to do in that process.  But it did not come from a mandated religion.  Reference the previous administrations stance on Gays in the military if you think I am off base on this. <p>---<br>
