<br>
RE: Prostitution - Why is it illegal to sell something when it's perfectly legal to GIVE it away?  <br>
<br>
A couple of reasons - TAXES being the number one reason.  Exploitation and oppression being the second.<br>
<br>
Drugs are bad, mmmkay?<br>
<br>
Drugs are also VERY difficult to tax.  The government can't have people trading money around buying drugs without taxes being applied.  The money that goes to the drugs WOULD have been spent buying beer which IS taxable and thus the Gov't has funds to arrest those that aren't paying their taxes.  HEY!  It's a CIRCLE!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Most drugs change the way a person thinks, and many of them are addictive.  These addictions often lead to life altering/threatening choices made by the person under the influence.  True addicts to certain types of drugs are known to become derelicts that would stab their best friends for cash to get a fix.  This puts them in a category of risk.<br>
<br>
Even marijuana has its negative sides.  I've known many people that smoke weed on a regular basis who are perfectly normal members of society when they're not smoking.  Once they get the buzz on, they become illogical, witless creatures that are prone to decide to hop in the car to get some munchies.<br>
<br>
While I agree that weed is one of the least threatening drugs available, and people tend to be more docile while under its influence, the impeding of one's judgement when making the simplest of choices is a key factor.<br>
<br>
I also agree that it's BS that alcohol is legal while weed is not.  They have very similar effects (in most people) and neither is really more harmful than the other.   <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.beaumontmachine.com/Assets/blindsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
